condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :1. Project Implementation Manual | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than one (1) month after theEffective Date, prepare, in accordance with terms of reference acceptable to the Association, and furnish to the Association, aproposed implementation manual for the Project containing detailed: (a) technical (b) administrative, (c) procurement, (d)financial and accounting; and (e) monitoring and evaluation procedures and arrangements, f | Due Date :15-Oct-2015

Finance Agreement :2. Appointment of External Financial Auditor for the Project | Description :The Recipient shall, not later thanfour (4) month after the Effective Date, appoint an external auditor, whose qualifications and experience and terms of referenceshall be acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :15-Jan-2016

Finance Agreement :3. Financial Equilibrium of the Urban Water Supply Sub-Sector | Description :In order to ensure the financialsustainability and maintain the Financial Equilibrium of SONES, throughout Project implementation, the Recipient shall implementall necessary measures, including, inter alia, any adjustments in water tariffs in accordance with the Water and Sanitation Law. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :4. Financial Sustainability of ONAS | Description :No later than December 31, 2019, the Recipient shall ensurethat all measures, including any required sanitation surcharge revisions in accordance with the Water and Sanitation Law are inplace to allow ONAS to achieve financial sustainability including covering at least 90 percent of its cash operating expendituresrelated to sewerage activities. | Due Date :31-Dec-2019

Finance Agreement :Sch 2.V.1 | Description :ONAS financial sustainabilityNo later than December 31, 2019, the Recipient shallensure that all measures, including any required sanitation surcharge revisions in accordance with the Water and Sanitation Law arein place to allow ONAS to achieve financial sustainability including covering at least 90 percent of its cash operatingexpenditures related to sewerage activities. | Due Date :31-Dec-2019

Finance Agreement :Sch 2.V.1 | Description :Tariff adjustmentsIn order to ensure the financial sustainability and maintain theFinancial Equilibrium of SONES, throughout Project implementation, the Recipient shall implement all necessary measures, including,inter alia, any adjustments in water tariffs in accordance with the Water and Sanitation Law. | Frequency :Yearly
